1
00:00:04,446 --> 00:00:07,026
You have 
to become acquainted

2
00:00:07,026 --> 00:00:09,986
to measure the value 
of any substance.

3
00:00:09,986 --> 00:00:14,536
You have to know the qualities, 
characteristics of that substance.

4
00:00:14,868 --> 00:00:18,658
[Spiritual Litmus Test]

5
00:00:18,761 --> 00:00:23,031
Or be in connection with
someone who does.

6
00:00:23,119 --> 00:00:26,359
So I’ve mentioned this 
in regard with

7
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:32,079
jewels, gold, 
and other things.

8
00:00:32,479 --> 00:00:36,363
Why do you think 
in the scientific world

9
00:00:36,363 --> 00:00:40,053
that they have so many tests?

10
00:00:40,053 --> 00:00:42,270
And the test, not only test,

11
00:00:42,270 --> 00:00:46,010
it’s not like anyone,
“Do this test at home.”

12
00:00:46,010 --> 00:00:48,497
There are some things like that. 
But other things …

13
00:00:48,497 --> 00:00:52,507
even to perform the test
requires an expert.

14
00:00:52,507 --> 00:00:54,465
There’re so many variables,

15
00:00:54,465 --> 00:00:59,115
so many subtle things 
to factor in and consider

16
00:00:59,115 --> 00:01:04,552
that it requires an expert
to conduct the test.

17
00:01:05,298 --> 00:01:09,318
There’re many examples of that
in Vedic literature as well,

18
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:13,158
and in the pastimes 
of Mahāprabhu.

19
00:01:15,408 --> 00:01:20,328
So parīkṣā, parīkṣit
means to examine.

20
00:01:21,898 --> 00:01:24,798
So to examine something
you have to be acquainted

21
00:01:24,798 --> 00:01:28,128
with the absolute standard by which
it can be measured against,

22
00:01:28,128 --> 00:01:32,388
and then you can 
determine its relative value.

23
00:01:35,301 --> 00:01:39,531
So minimally we hear 
asat-saṅga-tyāga,—ei vaiṣṇava-ācāra
[Cc: 2.22.87]

24
00:01:39,531 --> 00:01:46,573
asat-saṅga means 
bad association,

25
00:01:46,573 --> 00:01:54,203
but asat—
that which is no permanent value.

26
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:57,900
That’s why Śukadev
tells Parīkṣit Maharaj

27
00:01:57,923 --> 00:02:05,370
varīyān eṣa te praśnaḥ
kṛto loka-hitaṁ nṛpa

28
00:02:05,370 --> 00:02:08,370
ātmavit-sammataḥ puṁsāṁ
śrotavyādiṣu yaḥ paraḥ 
[SB: 2.1.1]

29
00:02:08,370 --> 00:02:10,646
But your question, 
my dear king, is very good.

30
00:02:10,646 --> 00:02:14,516
There’s a thousand questions
you can ask about anything.

31
00:02:14,524 --> 00:02:21,094
The temporary persons, places,
and things of this world.

32
00:02:21,094 --> 00:02:25,210
But you’re asking a question
that’s beneficial for everybody,

33
00:02:25,210 --> 00:02:31,897
because it transcends the temporality 
of mundane existence.

34
00:02:31,897 --> 00:02:35,455
So, everyone will benefit by hearing
the answer to this question.

35
00:02:35,455 --> 00:02:38,848
asat—that which is temporal,

36
00:02:38,848 --> 00:02:41,958
temporary is not the focal point

37
00:02:41,958 --> 00:02:46,608
of people who are serious 
about spiritual culture.

38
00:02:46,899 --> 00:02:49,680
They are focused on sat,

39
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:56,680
that which is permanent, 
eternal, spiritual in nature.

40
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,860
Hare Kṛṣṇa.

